## Convention Rules

### Files

```
WHEN creating component files
USE: {{COMPONENT_FILE_CASE}} (e.g., UserProfile.tsx)
NOT: {{WRONG_COMPONENT_CASE}} (e.g., user-profile.tsx, userProfile.tsx)

WHEN creating utility files
USE: {{UTILITY_FILE_CASE}} (e.g., formatDate.ts)
NOT: {{WRONG_UTILITY_CASE}}

WHEN creating test files
USE: {{TEST_FILE_PATTERN}} (e.g., UserProfile.test.tsx)
NOT: {{WRONG_TEST_PATTERN}}
```

### Code

```
WHEN naming variables
USE: {{VARIABLE_CASE}} (e.g., userName, isLoading)
NOT: {{WRONG_VARIABLE_CASE}}

WHEN naming functions
USE: {{FUNCTION_CASE}} (e.g., getUserById, handleSubmit)
NOT: {{WRONG_FUNCTION_CASE}}

WHEN naming constants
USE: {{CONSTANT_CASE}} (e.g., MAX_RETRIES, API_BASE_URL)
NOT: {{WRONG_CONSTANT_CASE}}

WHEN naming types/interfaces
USE: {{TYPE_CASE}} (e.g., UserProfile, ApiResponse)
NOT: {{WRONG_TYPE_CASE}}
```

